The Rhizosolenia emensis, stated by LEVANDER to occur in the two Finlandian lakes quoted above, is not typicaL as it has the connecting zone much more closely striate, with 8—10 costae in 10 μ.. Original specimens of Rlziz. err-'ensis from Lake Erie, as well as the same species from Vanern, Sweden, have only 4—5 costae in 10 μ, The Finlandian form thus ought to be distinguished as a new variety, as HUSTEDT has done, With the remark, however, that this variety comes very near to Rlzizosolenia erz'ensz‘s var. morsa WEST. Maybe both varieties are identical.
